Reasoning: The paper deals with a problem in hypergraph theory and provides a polynomial-time data reduction algorithm, which suggests that it belongs to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the parameterized complexity of the problem, which makes it relevant to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of sunflowers in fault diagnosis and the experimental results suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the combination of the sunflower technique with problem kernels due to Abu-Khzam and Moser suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of computational geometry (cs.CG).
